name: Transferred to 3.1.21.4
classes: Site-specific endodeoxyribonucleases: cleavage is sequence specific (deleted sub-subclass)
comment: Transferred entry: endodeoxyribonuclease Bsu6633. Now EC 3.1.21.4, type II site-specific deoxyribonuclease. The name was misprinted in supplement 3 of the 1978 edition. Assumed to be the same as endodeoxyribonuclease Bsu6633I (see http://rebase.neb.com/rebase/rebase.html)
